external_knowledge:
Highly recommended content refers to content with a recommendation score higher than 0.75; 
Top recommendation scores are the highest scores for each content item, ranked in descending order; 
Most recent engagement types refer to the most recent 'like' engagement for each content item.

"most engaged content" refers to the content with the highest engagement count for each user; 
"top 3 content engagements" refers to the content with the top 3 engagement counts for each user; 
"average recommendation score" refers to the average score of the recommended content.

sql:
SELECT title
FROM content
WHERE status = 'published' AND content_type_id = (
  SELECT id FROM content_types WHERE name = 'article'
);
